OL,5, People caught with Class A drugs in    
OL,6, Scotland could be given a police       
OL,7, warning instead of facing prosecution. 
OL,9,FOfficers can already issue a formal    
OL,10,Fwarning for possession of lower        
OL,11,Fcategory drugs.                        
OL,13,FLord Advocate Dorothy Bain told MSPs   
OL,14,Fthis would now include Class A drugs in
OL,15,Fa bid to address the underlying causes 
OL,16,Fof Scotland's drugs death crisis.      
OL,18,FThe Conservatives said the move amounts
OL,19,Fto "de facto decriminalisation" of     
OL,20,Fdeadly substances.                     
